    "caption": "Stubborn is just another word for thinking things through.",
    "shortDescription": "Donkeys have a reputation for stubbornness, but they're actually being careful — they don't move when something feels wrong because they know they don't run as fast as a horse and can't risk a mistake. They have enormous ears that can swivel independently to catch sounds from far away. Donkeys form strong bonds and can become deeply sad if a companion they know is suddenly gone. Fun fact: A donkey's bray — the loud hee-haw — can carry over three kilometers in open country."
